The paper discusses consistency models in key-value stores, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The experiments are conducted on the Voldemort key-value store, which is a database system (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the correctness of algorithms and proposes a monitoring and recovery approach, which is related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
